01:17.000 --> 01:18.514
AP MCCOY: <i>It's like being an addict,</i>

01:20.280 --> 01:22.317
<i>I'm an addict to my way of life</i>

01:24.200 --> 01:25.634
<i>because it's like a drug.</i>

01:30.080 --> 01:33.551
<i>I'm an addict to riding horses,
I'm an addict to winning...</i>

01:37.200 --> 01:39.635
<i>But it wears off and then you have to go
chasing it again.</i>

01:42.640 --> 01:46.190
<i>It's all about winning,
that's what you're really addicted to.</i>

01:48.480 --> 01:52.918
<i>That's why you go chasing that...
That kick that sort of makes it different.</i>

02:10.320 --> 02:11.993
<i>I don't know where
the excitement comes from,</i>

02:12.080 --> 02:14.151
<i>just the riding and
jumping the fences and...</i>

02:15.720 --> 02:17.313
<i>With lots of other horses around you.</i>

02:18.720 --> 02:21.155
<i>You know that there's not much room,
you don't get to see much,</i>

02:23.240 --> 02:24.799
<i>there's horses falling around you.</i>

02:33.680 --> 02:36.275
<i>I suppose near the end, I suppose
the adrenaline is in winning,</i>

02:36.360 --> 02:40.752
<i>you know, I mean, that's all it's about,
it's all about winning.</i>

02:51.040 --> 02:52.918
<i>I think you have to have goals in life,
you know,</i>

02:53.800 --> 02:55.029
<i>you have to have something to chase,</i>

02:55.120 --> 02:58.909
<i>you have to chase the thing
that you can't ever catch.</i>

03:15.720 --> 03:16.836
(HORSE EXHALES)

03:23.080 --> 03:25.117
(COURSE COMMENTATOR
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

03:29.840 --> 03:31.877
(CROWD CHEERING)

03:34.520 --> 03:36.716
<i>I don't think I was ever really content
with my life,</i>

03:38.840 --> 03:42.720
<i>because no matter how you have a go at it,
no matter how much you try, you can't...</i>

03:44.640 --> 03:46.438
<i>You can't be as good as you want to be.</i>

03:46.560 --> 03:48.597
(MCCOY BREATHING HEAVILY)

03:57.280 --> 03:58.509
( BREATHING DEEPLY)

04:00.440 --> 04:01.510
DOCTOR: <i>Previous injuries?</i>

04:02.560 --> 04:04.040
MCCOY: <i>Erm, cheekbone.</i>

04:04.800 --> 04:05.836
DOCTOR: <i>Okay, left or right?</i>

04:06.160 --> 04:08.197
MCCOY: <i>Left, yeah, because I never really
got the feeling back.</i>

04:08.720 --> 04:12.191
<i>Left collarbone, twice I think.</i>

04:12.480 --> 04:15.791
<i>Shoulder blade... Can't remember which one.</i>

04:16.079 --> 04:17.958
MCCOY: <i>Sternum.</i>
DOCTOR: <i>Yeah.</i>

04:18.760 --> 04:21.911
<i>The ribs are... They've
all had a go I think.</i>

04:23.080 --> 04:26.312
<i>My back is fused from T...</i>

04:27.440 --> 04:28.556
<i>9 to 12.</i>

04:30.280 --> 04:32.840
<i>Done broke my right arm, um,</i>

04:33.040 --> 04:34.190
<i>radius and ulna.</i>

04:34.480 --> 04:36.312
DOCTOR: <i>Both at the same time?</i>
MCCOY: <i>Both at the same time.</i>

04:36.400 --> 04:38.153
DOCTOR: <i>Okay.</i>
MCCOY: <i>My right wrist as well.</i>

04:38.920 --> 04:40.957
<i>My left tib and fib.</i>

04:41.600 --> 04:43.193
I think I always get
kicked there a few times,

04:43.280 --> 04:44.509
- that's all that is.
- DOCTOR: Oh, dear.

04:44.600 --> 04:46.000
MCCOY: <i>And my right ankle, I think.</i>

04:46.600 --> 04:47.716
DOCTOR: <i>Never had a concussion?</i>

04:48.160 --> 04:49.913
MCCOY: <i>I've had lots of bangs on the head,</i>
DOCTOR: <i>Yeah.</i>

04:50.000 --> 04:53.152
<i>But I've always been able to function
and know where I am.</i>

04:53.680 --> 04:54.716
DOCTOR: <i>Yeah, okay.</i>

04:55.440 --> 04:56.510
Hands on the side of your thighs.

04:56.600 --> 05:01.356
MCCOY: <i>As my career developed and I was
lucky enough to become successful, I...</i>

05:01.440 --> 05:03.557
<i>It... It became a bit of a numbers thing,
you know?</i>

05:04.480 --> 05:06.597
<i>When I started off,
I wanted to be champion jockey,</i>

05:06.680 --> 05:10.356
<i>and when I was champion jockey then I,
you know, wanted to ride more winners</i>

05:10.440 --> 05:12.477
<i>then any jump jockey had ridden before.</i>

05:13.080 --> 05:17.154
<i>In 2002, I was able to do that,
I rode, 289 winners in that season.</i>

05:17.280 --> 05:19.317
(INDISTINCT SPORTS COMMENTARY)

05:23.480 --> 05:26.154
MCCOY: <i>Then you want to, you want to win
more jockey's championships</i>

05:26.240 --> 05:27.913
<i>then any other jump jockey has before,</i>

05:28.400 --> 05:31.199
<i>and you want to ride more winners than
any other jump jockey has before, and...</i>

05:31.680 --> 05:34.752
<i>Um, when I rode 3,000 winners,
I actually thought,</i>

05:35.080 --> 05:36.560
<i>I will be able to ride 4,000 winners,</i>

05:36.640 --> 05:39.792
<i>I had it in my head,
I thought this is achievable, you know?</i>

05:39.880 --> 05:42.031
SPORTS COMMENTATOR: <i>But as I say,
to be champion jockey 18 times,</i>

05:42.120 --> 05:45.033
<i>to ride 4,000 winners is incomparable.</i>

05:45.320 --> 05:49.030
COURSE COMMENTATOR: <i>Crispin is out
in front here, Crispin from Panama Petrus.</i>

05:49.200 --> 05:53.672
<i>Mountain Tunes still staying on, surely
he can't, can he? The final hurdle...</i>

05:53.760 --> 05:55.240
<i>And there jumps Crispin</i>

05:55.320 --> 05:57.471
<i>and Mountain Tunes and Tony McCoy</i>

05:57.560 --> 06:01.156
<i>now launching a tremendous attack
on the outside. He's done it!</i>

06:01.240 --> 06:04.517
<i>What a hero! What a sportsman!
What a jockey!</i>

06:04.720 --> 06:07.838
<i>4,000 up for Tony McCoy on Mountain Tunes,</i>

06:07.960 --> 06:12.637
<i>who played Crispin late and Panama Petrus
back in third place.</i>

06:12.720 --> 06:15.189
MCCOY: <i>The thing about records
is they always get broken, you know,</i>

06:15.280 --> 06:16.680
<i>they always get broken.</i>

06:17.160 --> 06:20.119
<i>So I want to make it as tough as possible
for whoever is breaking them, you know?</i>

06:20.680 --> 06:23.354
<i>Because in, you know, in 20 years' time</i>

06:23.440 --> 06:26.592
<i>if someone is champion jockey
for the twentieth time, I'll be 60,</i>

06:27.000 --> 06:30.198
<i>or when I'm dead and buried,
at least it won't annoy me.</i>

06:34.240 --> 06:35.720
CHANELLE MCCOY:
Okay, we're going this way.

06:39.520 --> 06:43.400
Evie, sweet... Sweet pea,
can you stay with me? Thank you.

06:43.480 --> 06:44.550
Put your thing on.

06:46.360 --> 06:48.875
Right, please... Please stay with me.
Right beside me.

06:48.960 --> 06:51.953
COURSE COMMENTATOR: <i>Our award for
this season's champion jockey.</i>

06:52.360 --> 06:57.480
<i>He's been the champion every year since he
started riding taking a conditional title</i>

06:57.680 --> 07:00.878
<i>and 18 consecutive champion jockey titles.</i>

07:01.040 --> 07:02.872
<i>He's won Gold Cups, Champion Hurdles,</i>

07:02.960 --> 07:06.078
<i>Queen Mother Champion Chases,
and a Grand National.</i>

07:06.160 --> 07:08.834
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
a huge round of applause</i>

07:08.920 --> 07:11.992
<i>for our champion jockey Tony McCoy!</i>

07:12.080 --> 07:14.117
(CROWD CHEERING)

07:18.760 --> 07:21.195
CHANELLE MCCOY: <i>I would love him
to retire at the end of this year.</i>

07:22.240 --> 07:26.120
<i>Because the races are run at a faster pace,</i>

07:27.120 --> 07:30.397
<i>so when the jockey does have a fall,
they hit the ground faster,</i>

07:30.480 --> 07:34.474
<i>and there has been a lot of bad injuries over
the last, probably, two and three years.</i>

07:34.560 --> 07:36.836
Is Daddy going to win this?

07:37.400 --> 07:39.278
Well, that's the plan, Eve, right?

07:40.400 --> 07:41.993
CHANELLE:
<i>The fact that we have two kids now,</i>

07:42.600 --> 07:46.389
<i>and I think the sport
has been incredibly good to him,</i>

07:47.040 --> 07:49.430
<i>erm, and he is 40.</i>

07:49.600 --> 07:53.196
<i>You know, I know it's very young
in some ways, but in his career it's old.</i>

07:53.360 --> 07:54.510
CHANELLE:
Hold on, here's another one.

07:54.640 --> 07:56.120
One more jump. One more jump.

07:56.200 --> 07:57.680
He just needs to get over this.

07:58.400 --> 08:00.073
Please, please, please don't fall.

08:00.600 --> 08:02.956
- Come on! Come on, hurry!
- (EVE CHEERING)

08:03.080 --> 08:05.231
- CHANELLE: Come on!
- (COURSE COMMENTATOR SPEAKING)

08:05.320 --> 08:07.915
CHANELLE: Come on Anthony!
Come on, hurry!

08:11.240 --> 08:12.754
Come on Anthony!

08:13.160 --> 08:15.038
COURSE COMMENTATOR:
<i>And on the day he's crowned 19 times</i>

08:15.120 --> 08:18.238
<i>champion jockey Tony McCoy
gets home in the first.</i>

08:19.800 --> 08:20.870
Whoo!

08:22.880 --> 08:26.510
So, yes, I would like him
to retire this year,

08:26.600 --> 08:31.117
mainly because of safety reasons,
and to get him in one piece,

08:31.200 --> 08:36.400
I don't want to have a husband that you
have to help out of bed every morning,

08:36.480 --> 08:41.395
and, you know, ideally, that would be...
Erm, yeah.

08:42.720 --> 08:46.634
SPORTS INTERVIEWER: <i>Can you sum up
what 19, what number 19 means to you?</i>

08:47.920 --> 08:50.719
You got to enjoy the moment, um, hopefully,

08:50.800 --> 08:53.110
I can win another jockey's title,
maybe win a few more.

08:53.200 --> 08:56.989
Erm, I know a lot of people have asked me
about riding 5,000 winners,

08:57.080 --> 08:58.594
and my wife would kill me for saying that,

08:58.680 --> 09:01.320
<i>but, you know, you got to give yourself
targets and goals.</i>

09:02.560 --> 09:04.153
<i>You know I've been lucky...</i>

09:04.520 --> 09:07.399
<i>I've been lucky to work with great people
that helped me win a lot, but...</i>

09:07.600 --> 09:09.114
<i>And I have a great agent in Dave Roberts,</i>

09:09.200 --> 09:12.557
<i>who books all my rides, you know,
so, um, you have to continue winning.</i>

09:19.800 --> 09:21.280
DAVE ROBERTS: <i>The season finishes
on the Saturday,</i>

09:21.360 --> 09:23.511
<i>it starts again, I think,
now on the Tuesday,</i>

09:24.600 --> 09:27.718
<i>you're back to zero
and you've got to be riding winners quickly</i>

09:27.800 --> 09:29.075
<i>if you want to be champion jockey.</i>

09:37.840 --> 09:39.160
Hi, Dave Roberts speaking.

09:39.240 --> 09:41.118
WOMAN: (THROUGH PHONE)
<i>Hi, Dave, I'll pass you over to Alan.</i>

09:41.200 --> 09:43.396
I'm just checking with Chepstow tomorrow...

09:43.480 --> 09:45.312
ALAN: <i>No, I don't run.
I've just spoken to Frank,</i>

09:45.400 --> 09:47.312
<i>and we're not going to run him
on heavy ground.</i>

09:47.400 --> 09:50.074
Okay, so AP won't be riding him
tomorrow like that.

09:50.720 --> 09:56.352
ROBERTS: <i>His kind of approach is numerical, if
any horse can win any race, he will ride it,</i>

09:56.800 --> 09:58.280
<i>good jumper or bad jumper.</i>

09:58.360 --> 10:00.317
ROBERTS: Was there anything else?
ALAN: <i>Okay, no thanks, bye.</i>

10:00.400 --> 10:01.436
ROBERTS: <i>That's what's got him where he is,</i>

10:01.520 --> 10:06.197
<i>the fact that people know
that he will always ride everyday</i>

10:06.280 --> 10:09.591
<i>if it's physically possible,
and that is the difference.</i>

10:09.680 --> 10:12.070
Yeah, very well, no, that's
fine for AP tonight.

10:12.360 --> 10:14.192
ROBERTS: Getting to the tally of 4,000,

10:14.760 --> 10:16.479
that's probably a lot to
do why he's got there,

10:16.560 --> 10:20.395
'cause either he'll go racing when a lot of
people, years ago, wouldn't have done.

10:20.480 --> 10:22.949
They would've took days
off, but not him, no.

10:24.120 --> 10:25.634
SPORTS COMMENTATOR: (THROUGH RADIO)
<i>Rushing round these</i>

10:25.720 --> 10:27.871
<i>little tracks, riding winners
for a couple of thousand,</i>

10:27.960 --> 10:31.749
<i>and that... Are those basically, are those
his championship months, aren't they?</i>

10:31.840 --> 10:32.910
COMMENTATOR 2: <i>Yeah, they are.</i>

10:33.560 --> 10:37.315
<i>I think what makes it extraordinary is
he's only got to compete against himself.</i>

10:37.400 --> 10:39.198
COMMENTATOR 2: <i>Yeah, he's still
willing to get in the car,</i>

10:39.400 --> 10:43.314
<i>drive five hours up to
Newcastle for one ride,</i>

10:43.520 --> 10:45.432
<i>turn around and then do it all over again.</i>

10:46.040 --> 10:48.077
(CROWD CHATTERING)

10:50.200 --> 10:52.192
(INDISTINCT)

10:52.680 --> 10:54.558
BOOKIE: Thank you very much, sir,
and the best of luck to you.

10:55.360 --> 10:57.511
TV REPORTER: <i>Yes, that's right,
I mean, we're betting on</i>

10:57.600 --> 10:59.159
<i>whether he'll reach 5,000 winners,</i>

10:59.240 --> 11:01.596
<i>this is the next enormous land mark,</i>

11:01.680 --> 11:04.593
<i>and, of course, when he got to 4,000,
we thought it was highly unlikely.</i>

11:04.680 --> 11:07.559
MCCOY: <i>It's all numbers.
It's only ever been numbers.</i>

11:11.120 --> 11:14.192
<i>It was about riding as many winners
as quickly as possible,</i>

11:14.280 --> 11:18.513
<i>and give them as little time to dream about
even being champion jockey, as possible,</i>

11:18.600 --> 11:22.913
<i>because the longer they have,
the more sometimes it can become reality.</i>

11:23.960 --> 11:26.714
<i>I always wanted to just sicken them
as quickly as possible.</i>

11:26.800 --> 11:31.158
<i>I wanted it to be over before it started
if I could help it, you know?</i>

11:31.520 --> 11:33.193
MAN:
<i>You know, and it's always that thing,</i>

11:33.280 --> 11:35.078
<i>he wants them to look across at him</i>

11:35.160 --> 11:37.595
<i>and go, "Oh, no, it's AP,"</i>

11:37.960 --> 11:39.713
<i>and that's what you do
when you're riding against him,</i>

11:39.800 --> 11:41.757
<i>you just think, "Oh, yeah, I've
got a chance, got a chance,"</i>

11:41.840 --> 11:45.550
<i>then you look across,
and go, "Oh, no, it's like Doctor Death."</i>

11:45.920 --> 11:47.240
(BELL RINGS)

12:02.280 --> 12:04.078
RACE COMMENTATOR: <i>And they're off.</i>

12:04.880 --> 12:09.591
<i>Lucky Prince is the first away being
followed by Chalk It Down and Dresden,</i>

12:09.680 --> 12:13.310
<i>they're chased by Black Sea King
and Valley Brig and as they step over...</i>

12:13.400 --> 12:15.039
<i>And they're rallying to the outside,</i>

12:15.120 --> 12:17.954
Chalk It Down, Dresden
also trying to get on terms,

12:18.040 --> 12:20.111
they make the run down
towards the final fight...

12:20.200 --> 12:24.479
<i>And Dresden is down! Dresden is down,
and that has left Chalk It Down in front</i>

12:24.560 --> 12:26.119
<i>in the hands of the champion jockey.</i>

12:26.200 --> 12:27.395
And going towards the finish,

12:27.480 --> 12:31.918
is Chalk It Down who will chalk up
his first win over hurdles.

12:32.000 --> 12:33.036
May be lucky.

12:33.120 --> 12:35.032
<i>Chalk It Down the winner,
Fancy King second,</i>

12:35.120 --> 12:37.510
<i>Braccus third
and Lucky Prince of Valley bring in.</i>

12:49.720 --> 12:51.916
MCCOY: You kind of set yourself goals,

12:52.000 --> 12:55.914
I was thinking if I rode 20 winners in May,
then that would be good, you know?

12:56.880 --> 12:57.996
INTERVIEWER: And you're getting there now?

12:58.080 --> 13:00.390
Well, I've ridden 21, so I'm thinking now,

13:00.480 --> 13:05.271
hopefully, I can ride 30 winners in May,
so the goal posts have changed quickly.

13:06.200 --> 13:09.671
I'll be disappointed if I
don't ride 30 winners.

13:10.200 --> 13:11.759
If I don't ride nine more in May you know.

13:12.840 --> 13:14.160
INTERVIEWER: And what happens
if you don't?

13:14.680 --> 13:16.956
MCCOY: Uh, that'll be
a bit of a failure, won't it.

13:23.960 --> 13:27.590
MCCOY: <i>I do worry about maybe
not being as good as I once was,</i>

13:27.680 --> 13:30.559
<i>or not having as many winners
as I should have done,</i>

13:30.640 --> 13:34.350
<i>or worrying that people might think because
I've had a lot of success in the past</i>

13:34.440 --> 13:36.875
<i>that I might not be as hungry
to have it again, you know, so.</i>

13:40.560 --> 13:42.791
<i>Or they might think that,
you know, his time is up,</i>

13:42.880 --> 13:46.476
<i>he's not as good as he once was,
which happens to every sports person, so.</i>

13:48.440 --> 13:54.277
<i>I will give it a go, and try to ride my
fastest ever fiftieth winner if I can, um,</i>

13:54.360 --> 13:56.511
<i>but, also, I wanted to be champion jockey
this year,</i>

13:56.600 --> 13:58.592
<i>'cause if I am, it'll
be my twentieth season</i>

13:58.680 --> 14:03.038
<i>and, um, you know, that's something I could
never have dreamed of being able to do,</i>

14:03.120 --> 14:08.673
<i>so this season will be harder than any
of the others to try and achieve that, so.</i>

14:10.920 --> 14:12.912
(RACE COMMENTATOR SPEAKING)

14:26.640 --> 14:30.554
<i>Tornado Bob from Don Quixote...
is rallying on that flat.</i>

14:30.680 --> 14:34.276
<i>Tornado Bob, Don Quixote with that...
On the line.</i>

14:34.360 --> 14:38.400
<i>McCoy getting it on close.
His fastest ever 50.</i>

14:38.480 --> 14:40.995
<i>Don Quixote gone up in the shadows...</i>

14:41.920 --> 14:43.912
SPORTS COMMENTATOR: <i>Does it mean
that he's got a target in mind?</i>

14:44.000 --> 14:46.276
<i>Maybe that magic number of 289,</i>

14:46.360 --> 14:50.912
<i>his best ever season tally, perhaps even
getting to that magic 300.</i>

14:51.400 --> 14:52.959
<i>What an achievement that would be.</i>

14:53.040 --> 14:55.191
MAN: <i>Is this realistic this season?</i>

14:55.560 --> 14:58.712
MAN 2: <i>I think it is, there's no
doubt about it, he's got to the fastest 50,</i>

14:58.920 --> 15:03.153
<i>he knows he's ahead of his schedule,
he'll have that marked.</i>

15:05.160 --> 15:09.154
<i>Now his next target will be 100,
then the target after that 150,</i>

15:09.240 --> 15:12.597
<i>then 200, then 250,
and then that magic number.</i>

15:37.840 --> 15:40.958
JONJO O'NEIL: <i>This time of the year,
he comes maybe once or twice a week really,</i>

15:41.040 --> 15:44.750
<i>just to school all the young horses, and
even the older ones just to give them a pop.</i>

15:46.960 --> 15:47.960
Ah ya do, yeah.

15:48.240 --> 15:51.438
I need this for a week, wouldn't it?
To be fair, to get in properly.

15:52.280 --> 15:56.240
<i>So he has an idea of which one he would
choose to ride if it came to that, you know.</i>

15:58.160 --> 16:00.197
You're gonna pop on Monday Gold first,

16:01.680 --> 16:04.673
and fill some trumps, Master Fortune.

16:06.760 --> 16:11.596
<i>He's so much experience and what he tells you
about them, you take it on board really,</i>

16:11.680 --> 16:17.358
<i>and nine times out of ten it comes true,
you know, so having him on is a great help.</i>

16:22.000 --> 16:24.834
- He seems happy enough taking the big ones.
- O'NEIL: Mmm. Yeah.

16:27.280 --> 16:30.910
Oh, he's clever, I suppose that's clever.
I like to see him do that.

16:33.680 --> 16:35.990
- Yeah, he's very good. Yeah.
- O'NEIL: He's good and brave, yeah?

16:37.120 --> 16:39.191
But intelligent like 'cause he is a bit...

16:39.800 --> 16:43.350
He was over the hurdle,
he was a little bit grabby, you know?

16:47.560 --> 16:48.596
Whoa...

16:51.280 --> 16:52.350
Whoa...

16:52.440 --> 16:55.956
O'NEIL: <i>He has the horses
basically talking to him really,</i>

16:56.040 --> 16:58.953
<i>and he makes them do
what they're supposed to do</i>

16:59.040 --> 17:01.555
<i>- and gives them a lot of confidence doing it.</i>
- Whoa...

17:01.640 --> 17:04.314
O'NEIL: <i>Not everybody has
that magical effect really.</i>

