01:25:24.640 --> 01:25:25.710
WOMAN ON RADIO: <i>Just a little bit of fun.</i>

01:25:25.800 --> 01:25:27.996
<i>We've got a lovely lady
called Julia on the line.</i>

01:25:28.080 --> 01:25:30.276
<i>- Now, Julia is a careers coach...</i>
- Right.

01:25:30.360 --> 01:25:33.239
<i>And we wondered if you decided
to do, you know, a proper job,</i>

01:25:33.320 --> 01:25:35.789
<i>not a proper job, but a different job,
uh, what you'd be good at?</i>

01:25:35.880 --> 01:25:37.837
- Not snooker.
- (MCCOY LAUGHS)

01:25:37.920 --> 01:25:39.115
Definitely get this one...

01:25:39.200 --> 01:25:41.271
WOMAN ON RADIO: <i>The first one
is a racing car driver.</i>

01:25:41.360 --> 01:25:42.760
CLARE BALDING:
<i>What are you going to do?</i>

01:25:42.840 --> 01:25:45.400
- MCCOY: <i>I'm not qualified to do anything.</i>
- (AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

01:25:45.480 --> 01:25:47.756
(BOTH TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:25:50.200 --> 01:25:52.840
<i>It's what you would want to do, chef?</i>

01:25:52.920 --> 01:25:55.151
MCCOY: <i>I can't cook.
I've never cooked in my life.</i>

01:25:55.240 --> 01:25:57.391
BALDING: <i>Never?
You've never cooked anything?</i>

01:25:57.480 --> 01:25:58.675
<i>You don't know where the saucepans are?</i>

01:25:58.760 --> 01:26:00.240
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:26:00.320 --> 01:26:02.039
BALDING: <i>Do you know
how to turn the cooker on?</i>

01:26:02.120 --> 01:26:03.120
- MCCOY: <i>No.</i>
- CLARE: <i>No.</i>

01:26:03.200 --> 01:26:04.919
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

01:26:05.000 --> 01:26:06.912
MCCOY: <i>I'm not talented enough
to do those things.</i>

01:26:07.000 --> 01:26:09.595
<i>It's much easier to get
on the best horse, with the best trainer</i>

01:26:09.680 --> 01:26:11.512
<i>and just go round the circuit
and beat everyone else.</i>

01:26:11.600 --> 01:26:12.875
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

01:26:12.960 --> 01:26:15.520
CLARE: <i>What did your mum
want you to be when you were little?</i>

01:26:16.280 --> 01:26:18.715
MCCOY: <i>A lot of things.
A priest was one of them, but I think...</i>

01:26:18.800 --> 01:26:20.359
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

01:26:20.440 --> 01:26:22.238
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

01:26:31.320 --> 01:26:32.754
Did you get yourself sorted?

01:26:32.840 --> 01:26:33.840
Yeah.

01:26:34.880 --> 01:26:36.951
- Didn't get to sleep.
- I don't think you'll get to sleep.

01:26:37.040 --> 01:26:38.156
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

01:26:53.080 --> 01:26:55.117
ROBERTS: There's a
picture for you. (LAUGHS)

01:26:57.960 --> 01:26:59.474
MCCOY: <i>I'm a total control freak.</i>

01:27:02.320 --> 01:27:04.312
<i>Control is what makes you.</i>

01:27:07.760 --> 01:27:10.036
<i>You know, if you lose control
you lose everything.</i>

01:27:13.240 --> 01:27:16.790
<i>Every part of my life
was structured and controlled, I thought.</i>

01:27:21.480 --> 01:27:23.312
<i>But I could never control getting old</i>

01:27:23.400 --> 01:27:27.360
<i>and that's what got the better of me
in the end.</i>

01:27:46.080 --> 01:27:47.355
CHANELLE: <i>He was...</i>

01:27:48.680 --> 01:27:50.751
<i>Obsessed about control,</i>

01:27:51.560 --> 01:27:53.438
<i>control of everything in his life.</i>

01:27:54.560 --> 01:27:56.040
<i>You know, with the horses he was riding,</i>

01:27:56.120 --> 01:27:57.440
<i>the number of winners he was having,</i>

01:27:57.520 --> 01:27:59.796
<i>controlling his weight, controlling me...</i>

01:28:01.440 --> 01:28:03.750
<i>Controlling our relationship.</i>

01:28:03.960 --> 01:28:05.474
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

01:28:06.480 --> 01:28:08.870
CHANELLE: <i>It, it was all about him</i>

01:28:11.720 --> 01:28:15.236
<i>and he became a really selfish person.</i>

01:28:15.640 --> 01:28:18.951
ANNOUNCER: <i>Ladies and gentlemen,
all of us here...</i>

01:28:20.400 --> 01:28:23.871
MCCOY: <i>I think you have to be selfish,
I think it has to be all about you.</i>

01:28:25.920 --> 01:28:28.116
<i>I'm really embarrassed to say it,</i>

01:28:28.200 --> 01:28:29.998
<i>but, uh, no one else in the world
was important.</i>

01:28:30.320 --> 01:28:31.720
- (CROWD APPLAUDING)
- COMMENTATOR: <i>What has been</i>

01:28:31.800 --> 01:28:34.031
<i>quite simply an extraordinary career.</i>

01:28:35.280 --> 01:28:39.479
<i>AP McCoy, today will be crowned
champion jockey</i>

01:28:39.560 --> 01:28:42.997
<i>for the twentieth consecutive season.</i>

01:28:43.640 --> 01:28:45.552
<i>You are showing your appreciation</i>

01:28:46.320 --> 01:28:48.551
<i>for a legend of our time.</i>

01:28:49.800 --> 01:28:53.999
<i>AP McCoy will now be escorted
into the paddock.</i>

01:28:54.880 --> 01:28:56.712
<i>Here he is ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:28:56.800 --> 01:28:59.599
<i>the one and only AP McCoy.</i>

01:28:59.680 --> 01:29:01.433
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

01:29:03.080 --> 01:29:05.390
MCCOY: <i>I think a lot of the time
Chanelle would think that,</i>

01:29:05.480 --> 01:29:07.358
<i>that I was a lot more
interested in my career</i>

01:29:07.440 --> 01:29:09.033
<i>than I was in my relationship</i>

01:29:11.280 --> 01:29:12.999
<i>- and in some ways she was right.</i>
- (CHEERING)

01:29:17.120 --> 01:29:19.840
<i>Yet, in some ways she was right
which is not a good thing.</i>

01:29:21.200 --> 01:29:22.520
<i>Luckily, she stuck it out.</i>

01:29:25.600 --> 01:29:28.160
<i>I pinch myself every morning.
I'm a very lucky person...</i>

01:29:29.200 --> 01:29:30.839
<i>That she... That she stuck with it.</i>

01:29:31.760 --> 01:29:33.592
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:29:35.120 --> 01:29:38.192
You better enjoy every
minute of it, enjoy it.

01:29:47.400 --> 01:29:50.950
MCCOY: <i>It's what made me happy,
it's what I wanted to do.</i>

01:29:52.640 --> 01:29:54.632
<i>Obviously there was times it drove me mad,</i>

01:29:55.760 --> 01:29:59.197
<i>but in a contradictory way
it's what floated my boat.</i>

01:30:01.400 --> 01:30:02.993
<i>And the more you win,
the more you want to win,</i>

01:30:03.080 --> 01:30:05.151
<i>the more that the need becomes greed</i>

01:30:05.240 --> 01:30:08.597
<i>and I think, I think you
have to be like that.</i>

01:30:10.680 --> 01:30:12.717
COMMENTATOR: <i>We saw him
walking out for the last ride</i>

01:30:12.800 --> 01:30:14.519
<i>and the smile was a little more forced,</i>

01:30:15.280 --> 01:30:17.078
<i>because he knows
that this extraordinary career,</i>

01:30:17.160 --> 01:30:20.551
<i>his way of life in a sense,
is going to come to an end.</i>

01:30:21.040 --> 01:30:22.713
Sweetheart, enjoy watching this race.

01:30:22.800 --> 01:30:24.359
This is Daddy's last race ever.

01:30:25.880 --> 01:30:28.475
CHANELLE: Archie, you have no idea
what's going on, have you?

01:30:28.560 --> 01:30:29.560
Yeah.

01:30:30.640 --> 01:30:33.235
He'll watch this when he's like 21.

01:30:34.640 --> 01:30:37.519
COMMENTATOR: <i>Let's remember that,
a celebration of a great career,</i>

01:30:37.600 --> 01:30:39.193
<i>but we want the headlines,</i>

01:30:39.280 --> 01:30:42.114
<i>we want the Box Office
to give him the perfect send off</i>

01:30:42.200 --> 01:30:44.669
<i>here, in the silks of JP McManus.</i>

01:30:45.480 --> 01:30:47.472
School, he's gonna do school runs.

01:30:48.080 --> 01:30:49.912
Has anyone backed him by the way?

01:30:50.440 --> 01:30:53.956
COMMENTATOR: <i>They jump away
and there's a cheer from the grandstand</i>

01:30:54.080 --> 01:30:55.560
<i>even though there in the back straight,</i>

01:30:55.640 --> 01:30:59.873
<i>raving black box office jumping
just in the midfield on the inside.</i>

01:30:59.960 --> 01:31:01.713
<i>Green yellow hoops, white cap.</i>

01:31:07.000 --> 01:31:08.480
CHANELLE: <i>I remember
coming home one evening</i>

01:31:08.560 --> 01:31:12.679
<i>and he was sitting there
just sobbing, absolutely sobbing,</i>

01:31:14.600 --> 01:31:18.150
<i>because he was so petrified</i>

01:31:18.240 --> 01:31:20.755
<i>that he wasn't going to be
champion jockey the next year.</i>

01:31:22.920 --> 01:31:28.473
<i>It was like looking at somebody
who was living in fear of themselves.</i>

01:31:28.640 --> 01:31:30.916
(COMMENTATOR INDISTINCTLY TALKING)

01:31:44.520 --> 01:31:46.318
MCCOY: <i>I used to think the demons
had Olympic games</i>

01:31:46.400 --> 01:31:47.675
<i>in my head sometimes,</i>

01:31:49.880 --> 01:31:53.999
<i>but at the same time
in a crazy, mad kind of way</i>

01:31:54.080 --> 01:31:55.594
<i>it's obviously what made me happy.</i>

01:31:57.520 --> 01:31:59.000
<i>It's obviously what made me happy...</i>

01:32:01.080 --> 01:32:02.799
<i>Torturing myself,</i>

01:32:04.720 --> 01:32:07.076
<i>trying to figure out why that
every time I went out on a horse,</i>

01:32:07.160 --> 01:32:09.755
<i>I didn't win, I could
never figure that out.</i>

01:32:12.360 --> 01:32:14.033
<i>Maybe I thought if I could work that out,</i>

01:32:14.120 --> 01:32:15.315
<i>then I would have been content.</i>

01:32:18.800 --> 01:32:22.111
<i>'Cause it's slowly started to register
that maybe it wasn't possible after all.</i>

01:32:23.600 --> 01:32:24.954
C'mon champ.

01:32:27.960 --> 01:32:30.156
CHANELLE: <i>I mean,
I wouldn't change it for the world</i>

01:32:31.080 --> 01:32:33.595
<i>because it's made him
the person he is today.</i>

01:32:34.120 --> 01:32:35.873
- Come on, honey.
- Come on!

01:32:36.200 --> 01:32:38.920
CHANELLE: <i>And it's made us the couple
we are today.</i>

01:32:39.480 --> 01:32:42.120
COMMENTATOR: <i>He will have to perform
just one more final miracle.</i>

01:32:42.200 --> 01:32:44.157
<i>And it doesn't look like it's happening...</i>

01:32:46.040 --> 01:32:48.680
Come on, Anthony! Come on!

01:32:49.440 --> 01:32:50.635
Come on, honey.

01:32:50.800 --> 01:32:52.792
(COMMENTATOR CONTINUES TALKING)

01:32:59.880 --> 01:33:03.396
<i>MCoy, who's won so many championships,
he gets the win.</i>

01:33:14.920 --> 01:33:16.957
I'm so jealous, I'm so jealous.

01:33:29.840 --> 01:33:32.719
Enjoy. Enjoy, you deserve it, brother.

01:33:33.520 --> 01:33:35.477
COMMENTATOR:
<i>Dave Roberts, his agent,</i>

01:33:35.560 --> 01:33:37.950
<i>the man who has booked
every one of his rides,</i>

01:33:38.040 --> 01:33:40.555
<i>for 21 years, here in Great Britain,</i>

01:33:40.640 --> 01:33:42.597
<i>is coming up the race course with him.</i>

01:33:55.200 --> 01:33:57.192
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:34:07.480 --> 01:34:08.880
MCCOY: <i>That is the end.</i>

01:34:10.200 --> 01:34:13.477
<i>That's it, it's, it's...
It's gone. It's over.</i>

01:34:15.720 --> 01:34:18.872
<i>As a professional jockey
I'm never going to ride a race again.</i>

01:34:22.520 --> 01:34:25.319
<i>I'm a has-been, I'm a
retired sports person.</i>

01:34:29.280 --> 01:34:30.760
<i>I don't see it as a second life,</i>

01:34:33.960 --> 01:34:36.270
<i>I probably see it more
as a first life really,</i>

01:34:39.040 --> 01:34:41.271
<i>the last was more a dream
then a life really...</i>

01:34:46.120 --> 01:34:47.713
<i>And I just woke up.</i>

01:34:51.320 --> 01:34:53.516
<i>So I might have lived a dream
but I'm awake now.</i>

